        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the TableMetadata data structure — holds table identification, location, rotation, and title. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Table metadata: page location, UID generation, rotation angle, title. \par \b Input\/ \:  Page ID, optional UID, rotation angle, title. \par \b Output\/ \:  TableMetadata instance with auto-generated UID. \par \b Links\/ \:  [INHERITS(5): Serializable, USES_API(8): ApiTableMetadata] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>uid is always a non-empty string (auto-generated with uuid4 if not provided) \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why auto-generate UID with uuid4? A: Tables need globally unique identifiers for cross-referencing from text annotations. UUID4 provides collision-resistant IDs without coordination. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added semantic markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
